##I can't go home. I'm cooking for Dr. Wuhan

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

The closure of the city blocked plans for migrant workers to return to their hometowns, where they faced shortages of food supplies and daily food and drink.
Chen Jing, a 32 year old from Shaanxi Province, works in catering at the Hankou Railway Station. Since January 26th, she and her colleagues and take out bikers have been giving away free lunches and dinners to staff at five hospitals, serving an average of 1,000 lunches and dinners a day.
In addition to a fourfold increase in workload, the retrograde group is also at risk of contracting diseases.

Chen Jing, a 32 year old from Shaanxi Province, works in catering at the Hankou Railway Station. Since January 26th, she and her colleagues and take out bikers have been giving away free lunches and dinners to staff at five hospitals, serving an average of 1,000 lunches and dinners a day.

Year: 2020

Location: Wuhan

Year: 2020

Location: Wuhan

Great changes have taken place in Wuhan since the city was sealed off. All the shops were closed, there was no one on the road, no cars, no buses, no subways. In the evening, the whole city is empty, giving a person a kind of very miserable feeling. In all my years in Wuhan, I've never seen Wuhan like this

In 2008, I came to Wuhan from Dongguan to work, stay for a while, feel very comfortable. I think Wuhan and Dongguan have a big difference, Dongguan Industrial Zone, usually you go out, outside can not see people. But in Wuhan, people come and go on the road, the evening is also quite lively. I was surprised and asked my husband a stupid question: Why are there so many people outside every day in Wuhan? Don't they have to go to work? What are these people doing?

I still do not understand these problems, so in Wuhan has been staying until now. I'm 32 years old and an assistant manager at Hankou Railway Station, where I've worked for nearly nine years. The first three years I was an ordinary staff, then promoted to deputy manager, the main work is on duty, scheduling, management staff.

On January 23, when the city was sealed off, I was on duty all night until January 24(Lunar New Year's Eve) at around 7:00 am. I thought I would go home to have dinner on New Year's Eve. I'm from Xianyang. I got tickets online a month early. It takes 12 hours to get home from Wuhan, but I'm always in a hurry. I plan to go back in the New Year's Eve, the first day at home to stay one day, the second afternoon to go back, the third back to work.

But did not expect, soon came the news of the closure of Wuhan. As soon as the news came out, I didn't think it was possible, so I went to my friend to confirm that his shop was closed, and it seemed that it was really closed. I had to return the train ticket, call my daughter, said her mother can not go home, she cried at home. I said it's fine. I'll go back with you when Wuhan is unsealed.

I rarely go out, living in a restaurant and living in a two-point line, but also rarely pay attention to things outside. After the city was closed, public transport stopped and I had to walk to work. My home is only three kilometers from the Hankou Railway Station, and I walk very fast, for forty 10 minutes a day.

My family is in the opposite direction to the south China Seafood Market, and because my family doesn't like meat, I never go to the south China seafood market. But I've heard that the south China seafood market is selling jellyfish and whatnot.

At the end of December, I heard that there was something wrong with the south China seafood market and it was blocked, but I didn't expect it to be that serious. On the 12th of January twenty-six, when I was at work, I found a lot of people wearing masks to the restaurant, so I knew about the outbreak, and the next day there was an outbreak notice in the restaurant.

New Year's Eve this day after the night shift, I about 10:00 AM home, go back to bed immediately. I woke up at around four o'clock in the afternoon and found that the manager had called me several times and asked me to count the employees of the restaurant in Wuhan. A letter from Wuhan, food supply, staff food and drink have become a problem, the restaurant also temporarily closed. A phone call from the store manager made me think it was serious.

I didn't go out that night, and when I woke up, I couldn't sleep, so I kept watching the news on my phone. For New Year's Eve dinner, I ate a bowl of instant noodles alone. My daughter came to see us in Wuhan years ago. On January th, she went back home with her husband, so now I am the only one in Wuhan.

The biggest fear is that I suddenly woke up at three o'clock in the morning, saw a lot of video and news about the hospital, mouth mask, the lack of this and that, the heart is so sick.

I didn't go out for the next two days. Every day to see the latest news of pneumonia in Wuhan, the more I see the more heart-cold. If you can't stand it, talk to someone or watch TV for a while, but you can't watch TV.

There was hardly any other food in the house, but luckily I bought a box of instant noodles in advance. So I eat instant noodles every day, plus the panic outside, also dare not go out. Fortunately, the leadership told me to go to work, or I would have mold at home, even if not mold, because this person is not in a good mood.

January 26(the second day of the first month) at 6:00 pm, the store manager called me to work, said to the front-line doctors and nurses to send food, I said yes. She said it was voluntary. I said it was fine. I went to work. The manager added that he would have to prepare more than 1,000 meals the next day. I said, the restaurant might not have enough. I'll check it out.

I hung up the phone, and I left. This is the first time I've been out since I was 30. I put on the disposable face mask issued by the restaurant, and put on my gloves, hat, glasses, everything I could wear. To be honest, I'm worried about getting infected, too. But I think the doctors and the nurses are going to touch the patients, and we're just packing up in the dining room.

At six o'clock in the evening, it was getting dark in Wuhan. There's hardly anyone on the road. I went downstairs to the door and thought, oh my God, there's no one here. I felt so bad, I looked around while I was walking, this one closed, that one closed. I walked up to the overpass, suddenly met a person, wearing a mask, I think it is very strange, someone can go out for a walk, may stay at home too long.

Then go straight ahead, look at the road again no one, no car, wait until you get to the train station, shops are all closed. Only a few lights were on in the next street, and it was gray.

I had never seen a railway station like this, except for the security of the Station Square, where no one could be seen. In my impression, there are always a lot of people in the railway station. I climbed to the restaurant on the second floor of the train station and saw one or two people hanging around. I went to the store to check the merchandise, and I'll be back soon. I got home around 7:00 and made myself a bowl of instant noodles.

In addition to me, the manager of the restaurant asked me to ask other employees to come back to work. I said I'd try. I usually get along with my employees well, because I also started from the employees, I understand them very well, as long as I can help them, I will help.

But I'm not sure if they want to. Because of this disease, the whole city of Wuhan has been closed down. And I was thinking, how am I supposed to convince an employee if they don't want to? But I really didn't expect them to be so good.

I first call Uncle Pei, I said uncle, the leader wants us to work tomorrow, may have to pack more than a thousand copies. Uncle didn't ask any questions, just said, well, good! I thought, uncle is so brave! Everyone else just said yes.

There's five of us now, all volunteers. They are very honest people, and I are the same, from other places to work in Wuhan. They don't worry. They just say, "protect yourself. ".

Restaurant staff prepare food

We go to work now, and everyone has to wear a suit, a mask, one day at a time. You're going to go out, you're going to come in from the outside, and you're going to disinfect all of your clothes, including your mask.

The restaurant is usually disinfected, but after this incident, it's more frequent and careful. As soon as the employees go out, they come in, they're sanitized, and the door handles are sanitized.

It's my job to remind them that masks change every four hours. Restaurants don't have toilets, and when they go to the bathroom, I usually stand in front of the restaurant and remind them to sterilize, and if they don't, I just spray them with a watering can.

It takes time to sterilize, and they're all in a hurry to finish packing. I understand everyone, and they understand me, and we want to protect ourselves without hurting anyone else. The remaining employees are very responsible.

When we go into a restaurant, we rarely go out, pack up, clean up, disinfect, eat lunch, take a break after eating, go to the bathroom, disinfect, and get ready for the afternoon meal.

No one is allowed in the restaurant except the staff. The first day, Meituan delivery boy do not know, walked in, we said not to come in, come in and have to disinfect. The next day we put a piece of paper on the door that said "no admittance" . If they come again, knock on the glass.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Riders at the window

We prepare free lunches and dinners for the medical staff. I know, there is Wuhan First Hospital, the Tenth Hospital, Hankou Hospital, Lung Hospital, as well as the gold and Silver Pool Hospital.

They set up a group, there are 15 or 16 people in the group, there are Meituan contacts, there are our store manager, there are our leaders, and so on, how many of their daily communication needs.

Now we need to supply about 1000 units per day, but only five employees, the workload is four times normal, so we are very busy every day. We have to be at the restaurant every morning at 7:00 a.m. until we have finished the whole day's supply. Home by 9:00 at the latest. 6:00,7:00. I'm usually the first one in, the last one out.

I remember, on the first day there were over 1,000 orders, and I didn't eat all day. Because it is the first day to do such a supply, is not very easy, is very busy, very busy, very busy.

The first 500 orders that morning, we were under a lot of pressure. You start at 7, but it takes at least two or three hours to cook, Cook, add, add, and then pack. And the first and second order time is very close, sometimes only half an hour or more than ten minutes.

We all have our roles to play. Stir-fry cooking, add rice soup dishes, packing bags, counting the number, sorting boxes, disinfection, moving things, all to do.

When the time came, I would urge them, I would cheer them up, I said, "hurry up, hurry up, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come,

We pack up, Meituan will send a few drivers, because the large quantity of food, to pick up the driver not only to drive a motorcycle, but also to drive a car. Then, in order to improve efficiency, we talked to Meituan and had them tell us a day in advance how much to pack in the morning, how much to pack in the afternoon, how much to pack in the first batch, how much to pack in the second batch, and how many to pack by what time.

We also have Meituan's people deliver delivery boxes to the door in advance, and we spray them with disinfectant before taking them to the restaurant 15 minutes later and putting them in food packaging. Wait until Meituan's delivery volunteers are almost there, then take the box out. Otherwise, we're GONNA have to resell it in our own delivery boxes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Riders carry takeout food to their cars

The leader says we may have to fight for 20 days.

But when it came to work, I was afraid to tell my family at first. They all think I'm at home. We contact every day, the first two days because too busy, back too late, no video, back to a Wechat, said asleep.

But on the fifth day of the first lunar month (January 29) night when they video-chat with me, I forgot to take off my work clothes, they see, said, you go to work? I said, "HMM. ". They're like, "you're going to work after this. ". I said it's fine. We do a good job at the restaurant, we don't touch the outside world, we sterilize every day. Family or... you might want to watch yourself. I said I know. Don't worry.

My family didn't think it was serious at first, but when they found out it was, around January 22, they started calling me back, and I said I couldn't go back.

My 12 year old daughter is waiting for me back home. She grew up with me in Wuhan, but in the third or fourth grade, I sent her back to Shaanxi to study, now in the sixth grade. We only see each other once or twice a year. Sometimes when I can't go back, my daughter comes to see me.

She was practically raised in the shop, and all the restaurant managers in Wuhan knew her. She used to come to the store during the summer holidays.

One year, I remember very clearly, she was three or four years old, I was still employees, she said mom you are very tired Ah, you sit, I help you wipe the table. She disinfected the towel herself, ran to wipe the table, there are two young girls sitting there, she said sister you make way, I will clean the black one below. At the time, I thought my daughter was so sensible.

Another year, she was a teenager, I work very busy, no time to wash chopsticks, chopsticks, package chopsticks, she helped me, sometimes she helped me store those plates.

She cried yesterday when she couldn't get through on the phone. When we got in touch, she asked me, "what's wrong with mom? Is She sick or isolated? ". I said I'm fine. Today, she sent me another message on Wechat, saying, "mom, grandma cried after reading your Weibo. ". There was an article in the store about some of our employees, and my mother-in-law saw it.

I'm actually worried about my family. Before the New Year's Eve, I let them all go to the hospital for a check-up, checked the blood routine, everything is normal, I just rest assured.

Since I came to work, all staff know, leaders, friends also know, one by one call me, send Wechat, I have no time to return them. I appreciate their concern, but I really don't have time to respond. Two days ago, I posted a status in the friend circle, said "the two days are very busy, not back to everyone's wechat and phone, please forgive me. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medical staff stand in line for food

I was too busy to cook, either. At the end of the day, I went back to lie there, paralyzed. The shops close in the morning and there is no breakfast. The other day, uncle got up early, fried rice at home, but also brought me A.

Now people in panic, who have a tickle in the throat, a cough to scare people. Uncle had a sore throat, a little sore throat, today he coughed twice in the shop, I said uncle you don't cough. He laughed. He did it on purpose. He was just trying to lighten the mood.

Now every day on the road, see no one, I feel so sad. Wuhan these two days out of the sun, it seems to have a few people will come out activities. I'm scared, too. I'M GONNA take a look at this guy, I'm GonNa take a look at that guy. Every time I come back from work, when I'm done, I worry the most when I'm sitting here by myself.

I just think now, this disease in the past, quickly unseal Wuhan, then you can see a lot of people.

- END -

Dictation | Yang Jing
